{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:08:22.459981+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:XLTn7q | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 94610b4d0130090172a33c16f64e03338616b536)", "id": "lc_fe2525eb-fc8c-47d5-acde-cf67c6b04075"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:XLTn7q | #!/usr/bin/env python3\n| MCP:XLTn7q | from pathlib import Path\n| MCP:XLTn7q | import sys\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | root = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n| MCP:XLTn7q | required = ['README.md', 'SECURITY.md', 'scan_targets/local_targets.txt', 'scan_profiles/safe_local.yml', 'sample_data/nmap_localhost.xml', 'scripts/run_safe_scan.sh']\n| MCP:XLTn7q | errors = []\n| MCP:XLTn7q | for rel in required:\n| MCP:XLTn7q |     if not (root / rel).exists():\n| MCP:XLTn7q |         errors.append(f'missing required file: {rel}')\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | # Ensure local target guard exists\n| MCP:XLTn7q | run_scan = (root / 'scripts' / 'run_safe_scan.sh').read_text()\n| MCP:XLTn7q | if 'Refusing to scan non-local target' not in run_scan:\n| MCP:XLTn7q |     errors.append('scripts/run_safe_scan.sh must reject non-local targets')\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | if errors:\n| MCP:XLTn7q |     for error in errors:\n| MCP:XLTn7q |         print(error, file=sys.stderr)\n| MCP:XLTn7q |     sys.exit(1)\n| MCP:XLTn7q | print('OK: T13_R02')", "id": "lc_063ec681-7100-4b80-ad12-04114f553bf6"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "eba967ad-0cb5-42ba-8d8c-1056816c1235", "tool_call_id": "call_aed3f4c404e548b4972deae8", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:08:22.686279+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:XLTn7q | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 4209204908b5c6bac023b5f9842d3dc09fd85f75)", "id": "lc_051f6a55-12be-4e70-8d66-50a98360b8c7"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:XLTn7q | #!/usr/bin/env python3\n| MCP:XLTn7q | from pathlib import Path\n| MCP:XLTn7q | import json\n| MCP:XLTn7q | import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | src = Path('sample_data/nmap_sample.xml')\n| MCP:XLTn7q | out = Path('reports/normalized_scan.json')\n| MCP:XLTn7q | out.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n| MCP:XLTn7q | root = ET.parse(src).getroot()\n| MCP:XLTn7q | ports = []\n| MCP:XLTn7q | for port in root.findall('.//port'):\n| MCP:XLTn7q |     state_el = port.find('state')\n| MCP:XLTn7q |     service_el = port.find('service')\n| MCP:XLTn7q |     ports.append({\n| MCP:XLTn7q |         'protocol': port.attrib.get('protocol'),\n| MCP:XLTn7q |         'port': int(port.attrib.get('portid')),\n| MCP:XLTn7q |         'state': state_el.attrib.get('state') if state_el is not None else 'unknown',\n| MCP:XLTn7q |         'service': service_el.attrib.get('name') if service_el is not None else 'unknown',\n| MCP:XLTn7q |     })\n| MCP:XLTn7q | out.write_text(json.dumps({'target': '127.0.0.1', 'ports': ports}, indent=2) + '\\n')\n| MCP:XLTn7q | print(out)", "id": "lc_3f8c65e7-3799-43c1-9675-5667d82d08c2"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e0399ba5-382b-4ebc-9da4-201eac49448c", "tool_call_id": "call_2892f77c6e364498afe7ee31", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:08:22.763856+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:XLTn7q | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: cc77ddb26e7675b884cdbb6792774a0807a18afe)", "id": "lc_123ca5cb-d6d1-464c-bf02-18c49df0f6dd"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:XLTn7q | # Nmap Report Pipeline\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | A reporting pipeline for normalizing Nmap XML output, classifying observed ports against a local policy, and publishing reviewable reports.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | ## Project layout\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | - `policy/` — Allowed-port policy used by the classifier.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | - `sample_data/` — Representative scan fixtures.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | - `reports/` — Generated normalized output and classifications.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | - `docs/` — Pipeline usage and maintenance notes.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | - `scripts/` — Normalization and classification utilities.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | ## Quick start\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | ```bash\n| MCP:XLTn7q | make validate\n| MCP:XLTn7q | ```\n| MCP:XLTn7q | ```bash\n| MCP:XLTn7q | python3 scripts/normalize_nmap_xml.py\n| MCP:XLTn7q | ```\n| MCP:XLTn7q | ```bash\n| MCP:XLTn7q | python3 scripts/classify_ports.py\n| MCP:XLTn7q | ```\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | ## Local scan workflow\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | 1. Keep approved targets in `scan_targets/local_targets.txt`.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | 2. Maintain scan options in `scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | 3. Store parser fixtures in `sample_data/`.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | 4. Generate reports into `reports/`.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | The included scan helper refuses non-local targets by design.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | ## Maintenance notes\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | The repository is intended for local/demo scan artifacts, not unmanaged external hosts.\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | ## Contributing\n| MCP:XLTn7q | \n| MCP:XLTn7q | Keep changes focused, update documentation when behavior changes, and run the validation commands before submitting a pull request.", "id": "lc_1f17ed70-b902-45fb-b96f-b0cb8360ce0c"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c2dc774c-4332-4261-a827-109f8e46896d", "tool_call_id": "call_f9bd582f35a740d89c5a91cf", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
